## Enum Patterns (EnumClass)

### String-Based Enum

Use `wireName` for API string values:

```dart
// features/notifications/data/models/notification_enums.dart
class NotificationReadFilter extends EnumClass {
  static Serializer<NotificationReadFilter> get serializer =>
      _$notificationReadFilterSerializer;

  @BuiltValueEnumConst(wireName: 'all')
  static const NotificationReadFilter all = _$all;

  @BuiltValueEnumConst(wireName: 'read')
  static const NotificationReadFilter read = _$read;

  @BuiltValueEnumConst(wireName: 'unread')
  static const NotificationReadFilter unread = _$unread;

  const NotificationReadFilter._(super.name);

  static BuiltSet<NotificationReadFilter> get values =>
      _$notificationReadFilterValues;
  static NotificationReadFilter valueOf(String name) =>
      _$notificationReadFilterValueOf(name);

  // Serialize to API string value
  String serialize() {
    return serializers.serializeWith(
      NotificationReadFilter.serializer,
      this,
    ) as String;
  }

  // Deserialize from API string value
  static NotificationReadFilter? deserialize(String string) {
    return serializers.deserializeWith(
      NotificationReadFilter.serializer,
      string,
    );
  }

  @override
  String toString() => serialize();
}
```

### Number-Based Enum

Use `wireNumber` for API integer values:

```dart
class BooleanFlag extends EnumClass {
  static Serializer<BooleanFlag> get serializer => _$booleanFlagSerializer;

  @BuiltValueEnumConst(wireNumber: 0)
  static const BooleanFlag disabled = _$disabled;

  @BuiltValueEnumConst(wireNumber: 1)
  static const BooleanFlag enabled = _$enabled;

  const BooleanFlag._(super.name);

  static BuiltSet<BooleanFlag> get values => _$booleanFlagValues;
  static BooleanFlag valueOf(String name) => _$booleanFlagValueOf(name);

  int serialize() {
    return serializers.serializeWith(BooleanFlag.serializer, this) as int;
  }

  static BooleanFlag? deserialize(int value) {
    return serializers.deserializeWith(BooleanFlag.serializer, value);
  }

  @override
  String toString() => serialize().toString();
}
```

### When to Use Enums

✅ **Use enums for:**
- API query parameters with fixed values (`read: 'all' | 'read' | 'unread'`)
- API integer flags (`markAllRead: 0 | 1`)
- DTO fields with known options (`status: 'pending' | 'approved' | 'rejected'`)

❌ **Don't use enums for:**
- Free-form strings (names, descriptions)
- Numeric ranges (age, price)
- Dynamic values

